        <abstract>
            <p>Responds to CD’s queries on polygamy in birds and orang.</p>
            <p>Discusses sexual selection and secondary characters; colours and sexual preference.</p>
            <p>Expresses his admiration for Pangenesis; it is superior to Herbert Spencer’s theory.</p> 
<p>ARW differs somewhat with CD’s chapter on causes of variability [ch. 22 in <hi rend="italic">Variation</hi>]. Thinks several of CD’s arguments are unsound.</p> 
            <p>Briefly discusses how natural selection might aid in producing sterility between allied species.</p>
        </abstract>
